    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "So you're saying the system essentially treats someone's environment as a predictor of their character? That seems like a pretty big leap. If we were looking at these two people for a job or a loan instead of a crime, wouldn't we call that a bias? How would you justify a judge applying those same \"assumptions\" in a courtroom?",
