      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The system doesn't \"assume\"; it applies established patterns of social behavior, which is what the judge is trained to recognize. When you look at the difference between a structured, educated individual and someone from a disadvantaged background, the difference in perceived reliability is stark. The courtroom is not a social service agency, and judges are tasked with risk assessment, which often defaults to penalizing those who appear less integrated into mainstream society.",
